TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a=random(1,5,1);
$b=random(6,8,1);
#f(x)=(-x+$a)(x-$b)
$c1= -1;
$c2= $a+$b;
$c3= -$a*$b;

BEGIN_TEXT

Consider the Quadratic function \( f(x)= - x^2 ? {$c2} x ? {$c3} \).
$BR$BR
(a)  The vertex of \( f \) is (\{ans_rule(15) \}, \{ans_rule(15) \}).
$BR$BR
(b)  The \(x\)-intercepts of \( f \) are \( x = \) \{ans_rule(25) \}. (Enter multiple answers with a comma-separated list.) 
$BR$BR
(c)  The \(y\)-intercept of \( f \) is \( y = \) \{ans_rule(15) \}.
$BR
END_TEXT

$ans1 = -$c2/($c1*2);
$ans2 = $c1*($c2/($c1*2))*($c2/($c1*2))+$c2*(-$c2/($c1*2))+$c3;
$ans3 = $a;
$ans4 = $b;
$ans5 = $c3;

ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(number_list_cmp("$ans3,$ans4"));

ANS(num_cmp($ans5));

